"Whisk together flour, baking powder, and salt in a medium bowl. Using an electric mixer, beat butter and sugar in a large bowl until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour mixture and milk in alternating batches, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Divide dough in half and wrap each half in plastic wrap. Chill dough in the refrigerator for at least 1 hour or up to 3 days. Preheat oven to 450°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. On a lightly floured surface, roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut dough into desired shapes with a cookie cutter and place on prepared baking sheet. Bake at 450°F for 8-10 minutes or until golden brown. Let cool on a wire rack."
